<think><details><summary>Thought Process</summary>



The error is at line 172 where `data={categoryBreakdown}` is passed to the Pie component. The issue is that recharts expects ChartDataInput[] which requires an index signature, but CategoryBreakdown doesn't have one. The proper fix is to explicitly type the label function and handle the totalAmount property properly. Let me check the exact error message again - it said:

"Type 'CategoryBreakdown[]' is not assignable to type 'ChartDataInput[]'.
  Type 'CategoryBreakdown' is not assignable to type 'ChartDataInput'.
    Index signature for type 'string' is missing in type 'CategoryBreakdown'."

The issue is that Recharts expects data with an index signature. We can fix this by adding type assertions or by transforming the data. The cleanest way is to use proper typing in the label function.</details></think>
